<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><song><author>Don Potter</author>
<lyrics>[C1]
   Prepare the way,
   Prepare the way,
   Prepare the way,
   For the coming of the son

[V1]
 Blessed is the man whose Master finds doing
 His will when He comes
 It's time to start reading the signs
 That tell of the returning Son

[V2]
 Let us hold fast to confessions of faith
 And not be blown by the wind
 I'm holding on to what is written on my heart
 Longing and looking for him

[B1]
   In a blaze of glory He will come
   In the blink of an eye the deed will be done
   In a sky filled with thunder
   the clouds will part
   And on a white charger will ride God's heart

[V3]
 A voice is calling: Prepare the way!
 Make smooth the desert, God's highway
 Lift up the valley, make the mountains a field
 Then the glory of the Lord will be revealed</lyrics>
<title>Prepare The Way</title>
</song>